age. prestige. even gender.

259
00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:11.136
Then fingers get pointed at couples
who dive into love like that.

260
00:16:17.059 --> 00:16:19.478
I'm ready now for us
to deal with anything.

261
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:22.523
Are you?

262
00:16:33.492 --> 00:16:34.576
Yes. I am.

263
00:16:35.661 --> 00:16:39.039
Whatever it is.
I'll make it happen if it's for you.

264
00:16:39.748 --> 00:16:41.208
Tell me. what can I do to help?

265
00:16:52.094 --> 00:16:55.639
Do you happen to know
the location where people lie the most?

266
00:16:57.182 --> 00:16:58.142
In bed.

267
00:17:05.607 --> 00:17:08.193
Oh. I thought you had said
you were gonna quit smoking.

268
00:17:08.944 --> 00:17:10.988
The smoking pills don't agree with me.

269
00:17:12.197 --> 00:17:13.032
Oh.

270
00:17:13.699 --> 00:17:15.576
Chairman Shin of GL singled me out.

271
00:17:15.659 --> 00:17:17.745
She asked me to come
to Seongbuk-dong tomorrow.

272
00:17:20.539 --> 00:17:21.498
And so?

273
00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:23.834
And so…

274
00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:27.463
I told her that I quit my job.

275
00:17:28.088 --> 00:17:29.923
I just got forced into unemployment.

276
00:17:30.007 --> 00:17:31.633
Take responsibility.

277
00:17:34.803 --> 00:17:38.140
I'll find you something at the office
so you can start working soon. hon.

278
00:17:47.316 --> 00:17:50.402
I'm pleased you decided
to visit us here at Boudoir.

279
00:17:52.988 --> 00:17:54.865
Everyone get out of here. Right now!

280
00:17:54.948 --> 00:17:56.825
-Clear the room. please. Quickly.
-You as well.

281
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:03.749
Thank you. Ms. Choi.

282
00:18:12.299 --> 00:18:13.592
Did you know.

283
00:18:14.176 --> 00:18:15.719
since living here…

284
00:18:17.221 --> 00:18:19.181
…I haven't seen the sun even once.

285
00:18:19.264 --> 00:18:22.184
There's gonna be a cold snap
starting the day of the party.

286
00:18:22.976 --> 00:18:25.521
I wanted to have the first part outdoors.

287
00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:32.319
Hey.

288
00:18:39.284 --> 00:18:40.577
I wanna stop this.

289
00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:44.248
It grosses me out.

290
00:18:44.331 --> 00:18:45.415
The whole thing.

291
00:18:52.506 --> 00:18:55.884
Boudoir has properly established itself
by now.

292
00:18:57.094 --> 00:18:58.971
I'm telling Chae-u about it all

293
00:18:59.680 --> 00:19:00.806
and quitting my job.

294
00:19:06.353 --> 00:19:08.021
Why are you talking like this?

295
00:19:11.275 --> 00:19:13.235
-Kim Eun-jae.
-Sarah Kim.

296
00:19:14.236 --> 00:19:15.696
Call me Sarah Kim.

297
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:54.276
Yes.

298
00:19:54.359 --> 00:19:58.113
Someone left something at my door.
Um. I wanna review the visitor log.

299
00:19:58.739 --> 00:19:59.615
Sure. Just a sec.

300
00:19:59.698 --> 00:20:01.325
-You're in apartment 1102. right?
-Yeah.

301
00:20:02.743 --> 00:20:05.329
The only visitor is Sarah Kim.
according to the log.

302
00:20:05.829 --> 00:20:06.747
Sarah Kim?

303
00:20:06.830 --> 00:20:09.208
Yes. Sarah Kim.

304
00:21:37.296 --> 00:21:38.338
WHALE 2

305
00:21:44.177 --> 00:21:45.137
Yes. hi.

306
00:21:46.263 --> 00:21:47.556
Oh. did I wake you?

307
00:21:48.265 --> 00:21:50.475
It's just that I wanted
to ask you a question.

308
00:21:50.976 --> 00:21:54.062
You said your husband's president
of the Oxbridge alumni society. yeah?

309
00:21:55.272 --> 00:21:58.233
Uh-huh. Then could you look up someone
who used to go there?

310
00:21:58.317 --> 00:21:59.568
Name's Sarah Kim.

311
00:22:00.485 --> 00:22:01.486
Born in '86.

312
00:22:01.987 --> 00:22:03.071
It was

313
00:22:04.489 --> 00:22:06.533
an outright. albeit subtle threat.

314
00:22:07.534 --> 00:22:09.661
I'd already been involved too long.

315
00:22:11.288 --> 00:22:13.874
So she knew
I wasn't gonna report it or anything.

316
00:22:14.374 --> 00:22:16.418
Why do you think
she went through all that?

317
00:22:17.044 --> 00:22:19.838
She probably needed me
to scam Choi Chae-u.

318
00:22:21.381 --> 00:22:23.717
If she had even pretended to deceive me.

319
00:22:23.800 --> 00:22:26.303
I would have let her
keep thinking she'd fooled me.

320
00:22:30.265 --> 00:22:32.059
Like how I faked it initially…

321
00:22:38.482 --> 00:22:41.193
then fell in love with her
for real eventually.

322
00:22:46.656 --> 00:22:48.450
But she obviously knew all of that.

323
00:22:48.533 --> 00:22:50.494
She knew how I felt
and still did what she did.

324
00:22:50.577 --> 00:22:52.120
God damn it!

325
00:22:52.621 --> 00:22:54.081
You're gonna swindle me?

326
00:22:54.581 --> 00:22:55.874
Fucking bitch!

327
00:22:55.957 --> 00:22:57.459
Fuck!

328
00:22:57.542 --> 00:22:59.419
Stupid.

329
00:23:11.306 --> 00:23:12.724
God damn it.

330
00:23:23.068 --> 00:23:26.405
Hong Seong-sin.
Hong Seong-sin's number. Get it for me.

331
00:23:26.488 --> 00:23:28.073
I went to Hong Seong-sin then.

332
00:23:28.865 --> 00:23:31.910
I told him. "I actually conspired
with Kim Eun-jae to murder you for money."

333
00:23:33.995 --> 00:23:35.997
I said.
"You got played into a sham marriage."

334
00:23:36.081 --> 00:23:38.125
I told him the whole fucking story.

335
00:23:40.001 --> 00:23:41.294
And then. after that.

336
00:23:42.337 --> 00:23:43.672
a few days later.

337
00:23:44.506 --> 00:23:49.010
on TV. they said they found
an unidentified body in the sewer.

338
00:23:50.137 --> 00:23:51.847
I knew as soon as I saw it.

339
00:23:54.391 --> 00:23:55.517
It's Eun-jae.

340
00:23:56.893 --> 00:23:58.437
So Hong Seong-sin

341
00:23:59.646 --> 00:24:01.106
killed Sarah. you're saying?

342
00:24:01.606 --> 00:24:02.649
No.

343
00:24:03.984 --> 00:24:05.652
I was the one who killed her.

344
00:24:07.946 --> 00:24:09.823
I killed her. What the fuck did I do?

345
00:24:09.906 --> 00:24:12.492
Oh my God.
I killed Kim Eun-jae and Sarah Kim!

346
00:24:12.993 --> 00:24:14.494
INTERROGATION IN PROGRESS

347
00:24:22.586 --> 00:24:25.213
He was literally blinded by love.

348
00:24:25.297 --> 00:24:26.298
I don't know.

349
00:24:26.798 --> 00:24:30.343
It was exactly what you'd expect of a guy
whose job it is to fake emotions.

350
00:24:31.344 --> 00:24:33.054
Didn't you see the man's face
when he talked?

351
00:24:33.138 --> 00:24:35.056
If that was acting.
I mean. Jesus. what's real?

352
00:24:35.557 --> 00:24:38.935
Didn't you sense he was speaking in a way
that was only favorable to himself?

353
00:24:39.019 --> 00:24:41.396
Kang Ji-hwon is the sole recipient
of this entire con.

354
00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:42.981
which at least makes him an accessory.

355
00:24:43.064 --> 00:24:46.067
He's lost way too much to suggest
he's acquired financial gains.

356
00:24:46.151 --> 00:24:47.777
Not something to say while wearing nothing

357
00:24:47.861 --> 00:24:50.363
but expensive luxury goods
from socialites.

358
00:24:51.406 --> 00:24:54.367
"I was following orders.
I was mentally impaired from alcohol."

359
00:24:54.451 --> 00:24:55.827
"I am the victim here."

360
00:24:56.328 --> 00:24:58.205
Typical stuff bad guys always say.

361
00:25:47.504 --> 00:25:49.589
Ah. appreciate it.

362
00:25:51.967 --> 00:25:53.218
Thanks very much.

363
00:25:55.845 --> 00:25:58.723
I was suffering recently
from kidney failure.

364
00:26:00.517 --> 00:26:03.144
I only found out my kidneys were shot

365
00:26:03.770 --> 00:26:06.398
after they were already totally ruined.

366
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:10.151
At the hospital.
they told me there was no solution

367
00:26:10.235 --> 00:26:12.028
other than a transplant.

368
00:26:12.112 --> 00:26:13.780
But siblings

369
00:26:15.156 --> 00:26:17.659
that were born from the same womb.

370
00:26:18.493 --> 00:26:21.329
the wife I divorced. my estranged kids.

371
00:26:22.038 --> 00:26:24.583
God. even close friends
that I'd known for 40 years

372
00:26:24.666 --> 00:26:26.793
rejected my request for a transplant.

373
00:26:28.336 --> 00:26:29.713
When I was drowning in booze.

374
00:26:29.796 --> 00:26:32.424
behaving as though my life
was already done…

375
00:26:34.884 --> 00:26:36.344
I met her then.

376
00:26:39.097 --> 00:26:41.725
She worked under the name
"Du-a" back then.

377
00:26:42.601 --> 00:26:43.685
Eun-jae. I mean.

378
00:26:45.103 --> 00:26:47.314
I can't stand
the sight of you. so get out!

379
00:26:47.397 --> 00:26:48.690
Hurry up!

380
00:26:54.613 --> 00:26:55.739
Who are you?

381
00:26:59.367 --> 00:27:00.201
Oh…

382
00:27:01.202 --> 00:27:03.496
Well. it's past closing time now.

383
00:27:04.164 --> 00:27:06.124
Thought you should at least
settle the check.

384
00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:16.551
Get lost.

385
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:43.453
Go on. take it.

386
00:27:45.330 --> 00:27:46.748
Thank you very much.

387
00:27:55.507 --> 00:27:57.425
You're wealthy. Why do you live like this?

388
00:28:00.804 --> 00:28:02.138
Aren't you leaving?

389
00:28:05.892 --> 00:28:07.811
I'll give you something worth your watch.

390
00:28:09.729 --> 00:28:13.108
How I had lived my life
and how I was dying.

391
00:28:14.067 --> 00:28:15.777
I told her all about it.

392
00:28:18.113 --> 00:28:21.157
I guess I just wanted to talk
to anyone who would listen.

393
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:25.912
I'll be your donor.

394
00:28:30.417 --> 00:28:32.210
For 500 million.

395
00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:39.551
You want to do an organ trade. do you?

396
00:28:41.177 --> 00:28:43.430
I'm saying we should have a fake marriage.

397
00:28:46.599 --> 00:28:48.226
How can I trust you?

398
00:28:51.020 --> 00:28:52.522
Just pay after. then.

399
00:28:55.608 --> 00:28:58.903
And so
Du-a jumped headfirst into my dull life.

400
00:28:58.987 --> 00:29:01.823
where I had been simply waiting
for the day I died.

401
00:29:23.511 --> 00:29:24.971
RESIDENT REGISTRATION
KIM EUN-JAE

402
00:29:27.557 --> 00:29:28.767
Use that one.

403
00:29:29.392 --> 00:29:30.894
The first thing we did

404
00:29:31.394 --> 00:29:33.438
was get her a new identity.

405
00:29:35.398 --> 00:29:36.441
"Kim Eun-jae."

406
00:29:36.524 --> 00:29:38.026
"Kim Eun-jae."

407
00:29:38.610 --> 00:29:40.487
It was the name I gave her.

408
00:29:42.405 --> 00:29:44.657
That's how we became a married couple.

409
00:29:45.283 --> 00:29:47.035
No love. no respect.

410
00:29:47.535 --> 00:29:50.330
no reverence. no truth.
no duty. and no vows.

411
00:29:50.413 --> 00:29:52.749
That's the marriage we had just begun.

412
00:29:55.043 --> 00:29:58.254
In cases of organ transplants
between spouses.

413
00:29:58.338 --> 00:30:01.674
it is a requirement to have at least
one year of legal marriage.

414
00:30:01.758 --> 00:30:04.761
so we set the fake marriage period
to two years.

415
00:30:05.762 --> 00:30:10.058
Of course. our age gap was abnormal
in everyone's eyes.

416
00:30:10.642 --> 00:30:13.770
And even I would have found
the sudden marriage suspicious.

417
00:30:17.106 --> 00:30:18.525
Oxford. huh?

418
00:30:19.567 --> 00:30:22.237
If anyone questions you about your major.

419
00:30:22.737 --> 00:30:24.989
just say you paid
to have your thesis written.

420
00:30:25.615 --> 00:30:27.075
Shouldn't feign knowledge poorly.

421
00:30:27.158 --> 00:30:29.244
Wouldn't that create hostility?

422
00:30:29.869 --> 00:30:32.080
Because then I'm stupid and unethical.

423
00:30:32.163 --> 00:30:34.082
They'll overlook your ignorance

424
00:30:34.165 --> 00:30:36.251
and simply remember
that you had enough wealth

425
00:30:36.334 --> 00:30:38.211
to afford to buy your degree.

426
00:30:38.294 --> 00:30:41.589
They'll be more surprised
by your honesty than your denial.

427
00:30:42.423 --> 00:30:46.469
Claiming you'd graduated from Oxford
by having someone work for you.

428
00:30:47.136 --> 00:30:49.055
they'll have
the everlasting impression of you

429
00:30:49.138 --> 00:30:52.475
as a forthright and accomplished woman
who is genuinely wealthy.

430
00:30:52.559 --> 00:30:55.728
Naturally. in order
to convince people that it was legitimate.

431
00:30:55.812 --> 00:30:58.940
I needed to craft a story
that would offset all suspicions.

432
00:30:59.023 --> 00:31:02.151
If you're this smart.
why don't you manage your own reputation?

433
00:31:04.028 --> 00:31:06.573
You're very well known
for being a ruthless loan shark.

434
00:31:07.156 --> 00:31:09.450
Because that's what I want to be known as.

435
00:31:15.415 --> 00:31:16.666
Go out and do some shopping.

436
00:31:17.542 --> 00:31:19.294
Can't have you looking like a hostess.

437
00:31:23.965 --> 00:31:25.383
Please do not move.

438
00:31:25.466 --> 00:31:27.135
KIM EUN-JAE - F

439
00:31:42.358 --> 00:31:44.819
-Don't rub. Press down firmly.
-Okay.

440
00:31:49.240 --> 00:31:50.450
When I was young.

441
00:31:51.242 --> 00:31:56.039
there was a friend who teased me endlessly
about my family giving out daily loans.

442
00:31:56.748 --> 00:31:59.792
One day. that jerk had become
the owner of a failing company

443
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:03.046
and sought me out. asking for a loan.

444
00:32:05.757 --> 00:32:07.216
What do you think I did?

445
00:32:07.800 --> 00:32:09.010
You refused him?

446
00:32:09.510 --> 00:32:10.803
I did lend it to him.

447
00:32:10.887 --> 00:32:13.890
So much so that he'd never be able
to repay it in his lifetime.

448
00:32:16.184 --> 00:32:17.268
Enough for him to die

449
00:32:17.352 --> 00:32:20.063
and his son to inherit the debt
to be repaid.

450
00:32:22.607 --> 00:32:25.735
Then one day.
that man's son brought me that pine tree.

451
00:32:26.736 --> 00:32:29.989
Said it came from the family plot
where his father was buried.

452
00:32:30.073 --> 00:32:32.784
That it's worth well over 500 million won.

453
00:32:34.869 --> 00:32:36.871
I don't know what got into me then.

454
00:32:37.664 --> 00:32:41.584
but I wrote off the rest of the debt
in exchange for that pine tree.

455
00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:46.839
It was the only act of kindness
I ever granted.

456
00:32:47.840 --> 00:32:49.050
Kindness?

457
00:32:50.885 --> 00:32:52.553
How is that kindness?

458
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:57.809
Because I'm a loan shark.
and I backed out on being a loan shark.

459
00:33:01.562 --> 00:33:03.064
I wouldn't have done it that way.

460
00:33:04.148 --> 00:33:06.442
I would have promised it. but not lent it.

461
00:33:07.610 --> 00:33:10.780
You would win and hurt him.
and it would cost nothing at all.

462
00:33:12.115 --> 00:33:13.866
Continued misfortune

463
00:33:14.784 --> 00:33:17.578
is far less painful
than a ray of hope vanishing.

464
00:33:19.122 --> 00:33:20.373
Interesting.

465
00:33:22.583 --> 00:33:25.211
Loan sharking
seems more suited to you than me.

466
00:33:40.518 --> 00:33:42.520
I'll pay double in the near future.

467
00:33:45.565 --> 00:33:48.151
Oh. and why do you seem so unwell?

468
00:33:48.234 --> 00:33:51.112
Is it because your young wife
is draining all your energy?

469
00:33:51.195 --> 00:33:52.989
I guess I'm just too old now.

470
00:33:53.072 --> 00:33:54.949
Oh. come on. Get a grip.

471
00:33:55.033 --> 00:33:57.201
Anyway. kids today are shrewd.

472
00:33:57.285 --> 00:34:00.955
You think I'd get swindled out of money
when that's how I make a living?

473
00:34:02.206 --> 00:34:04.333
I've already had my will notarized.

474
00:34:04.417 --> 00:34:06.252
Oh. of course.

475
00:34:06.335 --> 00:34:07.336
Ah.

476
00:34:08.129 --> 00:34:09.422
I gotta take this.

477
00:34:16.095 --> 00:34:17.722
I brought you some tea.

478
00:34:19.182 --> 00:34:22.018
In order to convince people
that it was legitimate.

479
00:34:22.101 --> 00:34:25.897
I needed to craft a story
that would offset all suspicions.

480
00:34:29.025 --> 00:34:31.194
Just do as we practiced earlier.

481
00:34:32.070 --> 00:34:35.907
Today's goal is to make credible people
witnesses to our relationship.

482
00:34:37.784 --> 00:34:38.659
Okay.

483
00:34:38.743 --> 00:34:41.496
Don't try too hard to impress them either.

484
00:34:41.579 --> 00:34:43.164
It'll make you look desperate.

485
00:34:45.416 --> 00:34:46.793
Do I seem desperate?

486
00:34:50.213 --> 00:34:53.424
You're asking whether you seem
desperate with desperation.

487
00:34:54.383 --> 00:34:56.511
That's only because
that's the way you see me.

488
00:34:59.680 --> 00:35:03.935
We should create an underwater tunnel
that connects Seoul and Jeju Island

489
00:35:04.018 --> 00:35:05.645
and do it via KTX.

490
00:35:05.728 --> 00:35:07.438
Do you think the airport authorities…

491
00:35:07.522 --> 00:35:10.149
Not a single person
who was in attendance there

492
00:35:10.233 --> 00:35:12.985
seemed to doubt
Eun-jae's background or origins.

493
00:35:13.069 --> 00:35:15.571
That's why I bought the airport.
It was a no-brainer.

494
00:35:15.655 --> 00:35:17.782
When do you plan on supplying this. sir?

495
00:35:19.325 --> 00:35:21.119
Uh-huh. Yeah. all right.

496
00:35:26.666 --> 00:35:29.001
That guy seems like a con artist.

497
00:35:30.169 --> 00:35:32.755
When we met last time.
he said he was an equestrian.

498
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:35.299
Now he said
he swam across the Korean Strait.

499
00:35:36.342 --> 00:35:38.928
Next time. he'll likely tell you
he's an expert shooter.

500
00:35:41.681 --> 00:35:45.518
Last time.
you fronted him a large sum of money.

501
00:35:46.310 --> 00:35:48.479
You should probably verify his identity.

502
00:35:48.563 --> 00:35:49.897
Think so?

503
00:35:55.444 --> 00:35:58.823
Businessmen and con artists
do tend to be pretty much the same.

504
00:35:58.906 --> 00:36:02.660
But… there's just one thing
that sets businessmen apart

505
00:36:02.743 --> 00:36:04.328
from con artists.

506
00:36:05.246 --> 00:36:06.372
You know what it is?

507
00:36:08.124 --> 00:36:12.211
Even if they start out bluffing.
that isn't necessarily how it ends.

508
00:36:40.114 --> 00:36:41.490
What are you doing?

509
00:36:41.574 --> 00:36:44.035
You need to undergo dialysis
every six hours.

510
00:36:44.827 --> 00:36:47.496
I realize appearing weak bothers you.

511
00:36:48.247 --> 00:36:50.082
but you don't need to worry with me.

512
00:36:52.001 --> 00:36:54.670
-I'll get your buttons.
-I'll do it. Get out!

513
00:36:57.632 --> 00:36:58.758
You're trembling.

514
00:37:12.230 --> 00:37:13.981
Before I knew it.

515
00:37:14.649 --> 00:37:18.527
Eun-jae had become someone
who knew me better than I knew myself.

516
00:37:24.575 --> 00:37:25.993
About earlier.

517
00:37:27.662 --> 00:37:30.122
what did you say for everyone
to laugh like that?

518
00:37:31.582 --> 00:37:33.167
I complained about you.

519
00:37:37.713 --> 00:37:39.215
I see you had fun.

520
00:37:44.220 --> 00:37:45.554
It was sad.

521
00:37:48.224 --> 00:37:49.892
Because it was all fake.

522
00:37:53.437 --> 00:37:54.897
All of it wasn't.

523
00:37:57.024 --> 00:37:59.735
Occasionally.
when you let your guard down.

524
00:38:01.153 --> 00:38:04.282
you don't realize
your true self comes out. do you?

525
00:38:04.365 --> 00:38:07.827
You're even more oblivious
that that's who people like even more.

526
00:38:10.204 --> 00:38:11.706
That's the problem.

527
00:38:13.874 --> 00:38:16.127
Not even I know
where the fabrications begin

528
00:38:16.210 --> 00:38:18.004
and where the truth ends.

529
00:38:20.798 --> 00:38:22.883
I'm starting to get confused.

530
00:38:27.013 --> 00:38:28.389
Do you regret it?

531
00:38:29.724 --> 00:38:32.226
I only realized this
after I started living with you.

532
00:38:33.477 --> 00:38:36.147
Wealth is not a state of being.
It's an aura.

533
00:38:39.400 --> 00:38:40.860
And this feeling…

534
00:38:43.696 --> 00:38:45.656
would have been better left unknown.

535
00:39:01.255 --> 00:39:03.215
Eun-jae!

536
00:39:07.178 --> 00:39:08.220
Eun-jae!

537
00:39:08.304 --> 00:39:09.388
Eun-jae!

538
00:39:15.853 --> 00:39:18.439
I'll call an ambulance.
so be strong for me.

539
00:39:20.107 --> 00:39:21.984
You asked if I regretted it.

540
00:39:23.944 --> 00:39:24.862
I don't.

541
00:39:27.948 --> 00:39:29.325
What should I do?

542
00:39:31.577 --> 00:39:35.081
I've started wanting
to continue living as Kim Eun-jae.

543
00:39:42.129 --> 00:39:44.548
Eun-jae. Eun-jae!

544
00:39:51.514 --> 00:39:53.641
You're awake. Thank God.

545
00:39:55.935 --> 00:39:57.395
Are your kidneys okay?

546
00:39:57.478 --> 00:39:59.480
The moment she regained consciousness.

547
00:39:59.563 --> 00:40:02.483
do you know what the first words
out of Eun-jae's mouth were?

548
00:40:02.983 --> 00:40:05.403
Are your kidneys okay?

549
00:40:11.450 --> 00:40:13.786
Be sure to keep the funeral simple.

550
00:40:14.995 --> 00:40:18.290
Cremate the body
and scatter the ashes in my hometown.

551
00:40:19.041 --> 00:40:20.167
And finally.

552
00:40:21.335 --> 00:40:23.671
I'd like for all of my assets

553
00:40:25.005 --> 00:40:27.341
to be bequeathed to Kim Eun-jae.

554
00:40:35.516 --> 00:40:37.268
Your staff are outside now.

555
00:40:40.479 --> 00:40:42.356
They've all been waiting
for quite a while.

556
00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:44.066
wanting to greet you in person.

557
00:40:45.025 --> 00:40:48.487
I'm just gonna stop by the house quickly.
I'll pack a bag while I'm there.

558
00:40:51.949 --> 00:40:53.451
Get someone to do it.

559
00:40:54.994 --> 00:40:57.413
It's just
I'm restless being couped up in here.

560
00:40:58.956 --> 00:40:59.915
I'll be quick.

561
00:41:02.293 --> 00:41:03.377
Okay.

562
00:41:21.937 --> 00:41:23.647
Give him your thumb now. Come on.

563
00:41:26.066 --> 00:41:29.403
You better hurry. Make some money now.

564
00:41:29.487 --> 00:41:31.447
The day before the surgery.

565
00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:34.158
I found out the truth
about Eun-jae's identity.

566
00:41:34.241 --> 00:41:37.244
I found out that Eun-jae took loans
from loan sharks.

567
00:41:37.328 --> 00:41:39.455
which is how she ended up
working at a bar.

568
00:41:39.538 --> 00:41:40.706
CHAIRMAN HONG SEONG-SIN

569
00:41:40.789 --> 00:41:44.835
And that it was with one of my companies.
The One Capital.

570
00:41:44.919 --> 00:41:47.046
It was around two years ago.

571
00:41:47.129 --> 00:41:49.298
That bitch borrowed money
from The One Capital.

572
00:41:50.090 --> 00:41:53.260
We went to some department store
to demand payment once.

573
00:41:53.761 --> 00:41:56.889
We lost contact with her after that.
but here she was.

574
00:41:59.433 --> 00:42:01.143
She didn't stop by the house.

575
00:42:02.436 --> 00:42:04.522
I think the bitch already ran off.

576
00:42:05.606 --> 00:42:07.942
I would've promised it but not lent it.

577
00:42:09.235 --> 00:42:12.446
You would win and hurt him.
and it would cost nothing at all.

578
00:42:14.198 --> 00:42:15.991
Continued misfortune

579
00:42:16.951 --> 00:42:19.662
is far less painful
than a ray of hope vanishing.

580
00:42:41.809 --> 00:42:43.435
CHAIRMAN

581
00:42:48.816 --> 00:42:50.150
What happened?

582
00:42:50.734 --> 00:42:51.860
We caught her.

583
00:42:52.570 --> 00:42:55.823
She's been preparing
to stow away on a boat for months.

584
00:42:56.782 --> 00:43:01.287
She approached you with ulterior motives
to con you from the very beginning.

585
00:43:03.789 --> 00:43:05.082
Let her go.

586
00:43:06.166 --> 00:43:07.084
Sir?

587
00:43:09.003 --> 00:43:11.880
I haven't lost anything.

588
00:43:13.591 --> 00:43:16.844
I'm the one who agreed
to be fooled in the first place.

589
00:43:18.804 --> 00:43:20.598
So how is that a con?

590
00:43:43.912 --> 00:43:46.999
They say people change
when it's their time to die.

591
00:43:47.499 --> 00:43:50.502
I started to think
that it was all my karma.

592
00:44:10.564 --> 00:44:11.690
Why?

593
00:44:13.942 --> 00:44:14.902
You're awake.

594
00:44:15.903 --> 00:44:18.405
Why did you go through
with the transplant?

595
00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:22.076
You could've just let me die.

596
00:44:25.537 --> 00:44:28.457
Then you would have inherited
everything for yourself.

597
00:44:28.957 --> 00:44:31.794
Hmm. I'll wait a little longer
to get it. then.

598
00:44:33.212 --> 00:44:35.631
Judging how you look.
it shouldn't be too long.

599
00:44:38.884 --> 00:44:41.720
I wonder if Eun-jae
felt the same way I did.

600
00:44:42.596 --> 00:44:44.181
I'm not sure about that.

601
00:44:45.474 --> 00:44:46.975
One thing's for sure.

602
00:44:47.935 --> 00:44:49.478
At least in that moment.

603
00:44:49.561 --> 00:44:53.273
a con artist backed out
on being a con artist.

604
00:44:53.816 --> 00:44:57.653
KIM EUN-JAE

605
00:44:57.736 --> 00:45:00.322
And then she disappeared.

606
00:45:00.406 --> 00:45:03.158
as though she never existed
in the first place…

607
00:45:12.751 --> 00:45:16.088
…with a pine tree worth 500 million won.

608
00:45:16.171 --> 00:45:19.258
I'll contact a landscaping company
and have it restored within the day.

609
00:45:23.554 --> 00:45:25.180
Let's just leave it.

610
00:45:25.264 --> 00:45:27.349
Did she go through with the transplant?

611
00:45:30.686 --> 00:45:33.647
How the hell else
would I still be alive right now?

612
00:45:39.528 --> 00:45:40.779
MEDICAL RECORDS

613
00:45:42.698 --> 00:45:43.782
ORGAN DONATION CONSENT

614
00:45:43.866 --> 00:45:44.867
DONOR
KIM EUN-JAE

615
00:45:44.950 --> 00:45:45.993
RECIPIENT
HONG SEONG-SIN

616
00:45:52.166 --> 00:45:53.709
It wasn't there.

617
00:45:53.792 --> 00:45:56.003
There were no signs of surgery
on the body.

618
00:45:58.714 --> 00:46:00.299
Sarah Kim's alive.

619
00:46:07.473 --> 00:46:11.769
SEOUL METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY
PRESS CONFERENCE

620
00:46:11.852 --> 00:46:14.396
Hello. Park Mu-gyeong
of the Seoul Metro Police Agency.

621
00:46:14.480 --> 00:46:15.981
Violent Crimes Investigation Unit.

622
00:46:16.064 --> 00:46:17.399
Let's begin the briefing.

623
00:46:17.900 --> 00:46:20.569
The suspect has been confirmed
to have lived under false identities.

624
00:46:20.652 --> 00:46:23.530
changing their name. nationality. job.
and educational background

625
00:46:23.614 --> 00:46:25.824
at least three times over several years.

626
00:46:26.450 --> 00:46:27.951
Considering the intensity of the crime.

627
00:46:28.035 --> 00:46:31.330
we are issuing a public search
for the suspect with immediate effect.

628
00:46:32.790 --> 00:46:35.793
Anyone who knows the suspect's
real identity or has seen them recently

629
00:46:35.876 --> 00:46:39.213
is urged to inform the Seoul Metro Police
Violent Crimes Unit immediately.

630
00:46:44.092 --> 00:46:46.053
Do you know when we find missing people

631
00:46:46.136 --> 00:46:47.888
who have disappeared on their own terms?

632
00:46:52.351 --> 00:46:54.436
When they come back on their own terms.

632
00:46:55.305 --> 00:47:55.583
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.com ] ==-
